===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} {{term|letter|lang=enm}}, {{term|lettre|lang=enm}} from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|letre|lang=fro}} from {{etyl|la}} {{term|littera|lang=la||letter of the alphabet"; ''in plural'', "epistle}} from {{etyl|ett}} from {{etyl|grc}} {{term|διφθέρα||tr=diphtherā||tablet|lang=grc}}. Displaced native [[Middle English]] ''[[bocstaff#Middle English|bocstaf, bookstave]]'' "letter, alphabetic symbol" (from [[Old English]] ''[[bocstæf#Old English|bōcstæf]]'' "alphabetic symbol, written character"), [[Middle English]] ''[[bocrune#Middle English|bocrune, bocroune]]'' "letter, written character" (from [[Old English]] ''[[boc#Old English|bōc]]'' "book" + ''[[run#Old English|rūn]]'' "letter, rune"), [[Middle English]] ''[[writrune#Middle English|writrune, writroune]]'' "letter, document" (from [[Old English]] ''[[writ#Old English|writ]]'' "letter, epistle" + ''[[run#Old English|rūn]]'' "letter, rune"), [[Old English]] ''[[ærendboc#Old English|ǣrendbōc]]'' "letter, message", [[Old English]] ''[[ærendgewrit#Old English|ǣrendġewrit]]'' "letter, written message".

